    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1963-09-12T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1963-09-12T15:00:00-05:00" n="97"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d97">
                <head>97. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Vietnam</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d97fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, <gloss target="#t_POL1">POL</gloss> 1 S VIET. Top Secret; Immediate.
                        Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_HRJ1">Hilsman</persName> and cleared by
                            <persName corresp="#p_RD1">Rusk</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_SB1">Bromley Smith</persName>. Repeated to <gloss
                            target="#t_CINCPAC1">CINCPAC</gloss> for <gloss target="#t_POLAD1"
                            >POLAD</gloss> exclusive to Felt.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1963-09-12T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 12, 1963, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>391. Eyes only for the Ambassador.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Highest level meeting September 11,<note n="2" xml:id="d97fn2">See <ref
                                target="#d93">Documents 93</ref> and <ref target="#d94"
                            >94</ref>.</note> discussed your 478<note n="3" xml:id="d97fn3">
                            <ref target="#d86">Document 86</ref>.</note> and draft State Department
                        plan for multiple pressures, public and private, to remove <persName
                            corresp="#p_NHU1">Nhu</persName>s from scene.<note n="4" xml:id="d97fn4"
                            >Apparent reference to <ref target="#d89">Documents 89</ref> and <ref
                                target="#d90">90</ref>.</note>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Sense of meeting was that you should continue frequent conversations with
                        Diem, although all recognize how frustrating these are. On this point
                        Secretary will be sending you a separate cable.<note n="5" xml:id="d97fn5">
                            <ref target="#d98">Document 98</ref>.</note>
                    </item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>In the meantime we preparing plans for consideration highest level of
                        variety of concrete moves we can make to give you additional
                        leverage.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>Among these are the following: <list>
                            <label>(a)</label>
                            <item>Evacuation of all dependents, which strikes us as
                                desirable.</item>
                            <label>(b)</label>
                            <item>Senate Resolution, along lines <persName corresp="#p_CF1">Frank
                                    Church</persName>’s proposal<note n="6" xml:id="d97fn6">See <ref
                                        target="#d84fn3">footnote 3, Document 84</ref>.</note>
                                providing we are sure it will pass with large majority and will not
                                be amended so as to tie the Administration’s hands.</item>
                            <label>(c)</label>
                            <item>Phased plan of isolation Nhu, including giving aid directly to
                                units and programs and bypassing central government.</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <pb facs="0222" n="196" xml:id="pg_196"/>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>Re your 483,<note n="7" xml:id="d97fn7">In telegram 483, September 11, the
                            Embassy and <gloss target="#t_USOM1">USOM</gloss> questioned the wisdom
                            of delaying aid programs to Vietnam, suggested that U.S. policy make a
                            clear distinction between the Palace and the Vietnamese people, and
                            suspend aid only on projects which would affect <persName
                                corresp="#p_DIEM1">Diem</persName> and his immediate circle of
                            supporters. (Department of State, Central Files, <gloss target="#t_AID1"
                                >AID</gloss>(US) <gloss target="#t_S1">S</gloss> VIET)</note> in the
                        meantime and over the next few days while fundamental decisions being
                        formulated, <gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss> will stall on the major
                        negotiations or finalizing actions now pending.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">
                            <persName corresp="#p_RD1">Rusk</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
